## 4. Concepts (delta over the champion's ¬ß3; new terms defined here)

- **K0 / K1 / DIRECT / LOGGED / seq / tape / base / batch / token / slot /
  world / worldKey‚ÜímaskId (changed, ¬ß8.3) / NEWEST / RENDER_NEWEST /
  watcher / pass / pin / lineage / retirement / episode** ‚Äî as the
  champion, except: `worldKey` is replaced by **maskId** = interned
  `(deferredMask, lockedInVariant)` with **no pin component**; memos carry
  their fold-pin as data. `lockedInVariant` enumerates live locked tokens
  only ‚Äî the empty variant is the single-root/steady-state case, so maskId
  is stable across unrelated commits.
- **touchedSlots(n)** ‚Äî int32 cold column: bit k set ‚áî some k-write's
  influence cone, as recorded in K0‚à™K1 *at any time this episode*, includes
  n. Monotone per (episode √ó slot-generation); cleared per-slot at slot
  recycle via the touched list, bulk at quiescence. Replaces the scalar
  worldSensitive flag: routing tests `touchedSlots(n) == 0`; the fixup and
  the retirement ring test individual bits.
- **touchedList[slot]** ‚Äî per-slot append-only list of node ids first
  touched by that slot (walk or propagation appends on 0‚Üí1 of the bit).
  Bounded by touched-region size; the slot's retirement fold, suppression
  revocation, bit-clear at recycle, and quiescence zeroing all iterate it.
- **deliveredMask(n) / deliveredEra(n)** ‚Äî int32 cold columns: bit k +
  stamp meaning "a k-walk has delivered through n and no k re-arm happened
  since era deliveredEra(n)". **rearmEra[32]** ‚Äî per-slot int32 from a
  dedicated era counter, bumped when any watcher re-arms for that slot.
  Prune rule ¬ß9.2.
- **suppressedMask(n)** ‚Äî int32 cold column: bit k set ‚áî a k-delivery at n
  (watchers and descent) was equality-suppressed by the cutoff and is
  revocable (¬ß9.3). Cleared on revocation, per-slot via touchedList at
  retire/recycle.
- **baseSeq(a)** ‚Äî per-atom seq of the newest entry ever folded into its
  base (stamped at compaction; 0 for never-folded). Atom's version in
  world w = `max(baseSeq, seq of newest w-visible entry)` ‚Äî monotone
  across compaction (I16/B1 repair).
- **retire ring** ‚Äî global ring of the last R=64 retirements
